Vladimir Nabokov





TO: GLLBERTE NABOKOV1

ALS, 1 p. Elena Sikorski.





Montreux-Palace

Montreux

May 5, 1964

My dear Gilberte,

I understand what you are experiencing too well to try to send condolences. Believe me when I say that Vera's thoughts and mine are with you in the profoundest sense. The shock of losing my poor brother was a great one. I regretted very deeply not being able to come to Brussels;2 on the other hand, I know that, with that keen, charming sense of humor that made hi